JUST DRAFT PRIVACY POLICY

Last Updated: June 2026

Welcome to Just Draft. Your privacy is important to us. This Privacy Policy explains how information is collected, used, stored, and protected when you use Just Draft.

By downloading, installing, or using Just Draft, you agree to the practices described in this Privacy Policy.

Information We Collect
Information You Voluntarily Provide

We may collect information that you voluntarily provide when:

Contacting customer support
Reporting bugs or technical issues
Submitting feedback or suggestions
Requesting assistance with your account
Communicating with us by email
Automatically Collected Information

The Game may automatically collect certain technical and usage information, including:

Device type and model
Operating system version
Application version
Language and region settings
Anonymous identifiers
Crash reports
Diagnostic information
Gameplay statistics
Session duration
Feature usage information
Gameplay and Progression Data

To provide game functionality, we may store:

Account level
Experience points
Tournament progress
Draft history
Achievement progress
Collection status
Purchased content
Virtual currency balances
Settings and preferences
Sign in with Apple

If you choose to use Sign in with Apple, Apple may provide us with a unique account identifier. We never receive your Apple password.

Use of Sign in with Apple is also governed by Apple's own privacy policies.

Game Center

If enabled, Game Center may process achievements, rankings, leaderboards, and related gameplay information through Apple's services.

In-App Purchases

Just Draft may offer optional digital purchases.

All purchases are processed directly through Apple's App Store. We do not receive or store credit card information or payment credentials.

Analytics and Diagnostics

Anonymous analytics and diagnostics may be collected to:

Improve game stability
Fix bugs
Improve performance
Analyze feature usage
Improve balancing and progression systems
Enhance overall user experience
Cloud Saves

Where available, game progress may be stored using Apple cloud services to allow synchronization across supported devices.

Data Sharing

We do not sell personal information.

We do not rent personal information.

We do not trade personal information.

Information may only be shared:

When required by law
To comply with legal obligations
To protect users or the Game
With trusted service providers necessary for operation of the Game
During a merger, acquisition, or business transfer
Data Security

We use reasonable technical and organizational measures to protect information. However, no system can guarantee absolute security.

Children's Privacy

Just Draft is not specifically directed toward children under the minimum age required by applicable law.

If information is discovered to have been collected improperly, reasonable efforts will be made to delete such information.

